consent.text:
Remote Patient Monitoring Consent Form


By signing this agreement, you consent to your physician
(referred to hereinafter as “Provider”) providing remote patient monitoring services (referred to as “RPM Services”) to you as more fully described below.


What is RPM services?

RPM Services are available to you because Medicare want to keep you healthy, detect the unhealthy trend earlier which can be treated in timely manner. Medicare offers you to be monitored by your healthcare provider to Collect and interpret your physiologic data (e.g., ECG, blood pressure, glucose monitoring) digitally stored and/or transmitted by you and/or caregiver.


How to enter the elements of services?

RPM Services include 24-hours-a-day, 7-days-a-week access to a healthcare application on your smart phone, through this app, you could enter your physiological data to the data repository, which will be monitored by your provider or his designated train healthcare worker. Your provider will make management decision based on physiological data and would ask you to act accordingly

How will the patient’s information be shared among practitioners and providers?

Patient will have a care plan designed for him and will be available electronically in the EMR and patient portal Patient will have access to his care plan and will have the ability to share access to the electronic care plan 24/7.

Beneficiary Acknowledgment and Authorization

By signing this Agreement, you agree to the following:

  • You consent to the Provider providing RPM Services to you.
  • You authorize electronic communication of your medical information with other treating providers as part of coordination of your care.
  • You acknowledge that only one practitioner can furnish RPM Services to you during a calendar month.
  • You understand that that cost-sharing will apply to CCM Services, so you may be billed for a portion of RPM Services even though RPM Services will not involve a face-to-face meeting with the Provider. If your supplemental insurance does not cover the remaining cost, the remaining will be billed to you for the service.

Beneficiary Rights

You have the following rights with respect to RPM Services:

  • You have the right to stop RPM Services at any time by revoking this Agreement effective at the end of the then-current month. You may revoke this agreement verbally or in writing. Upon receipt of your revocation, the Provider will give you written confirmation (including the effective date) of revocation.
  • I understand that there are alternatives to a Remote Patient Monitoring and I may elect, at any time, for a direct consultation by any healthcare provider at any medical office or emergency facility

rtmConsent.text:
Consent for Communication Technology-Based Services (CTBS)

Consent for Telemedicine(TM),Remote Patient Monitoring(RPM), Chronic Care Management(CCM),Remote Therapeutic Monitoring (RTM) & Secure Messaging (SMS)


By signing this agreement, you consent to ,
(referred to hereinafter as “Provider”) providing TM/RPM/CCM/RTM/SMS (referred to as “CTBS”) to you as more fully described below.


Purpose: The purpose of this agreement is to take your informed consent to participate in a TM/RPM/CCM/RTM/SMS) and provide healthcare service which can be delivered to you using Telecommunication as allowed by the Law.


What are TM/RPM/CCM/RTM/SMS services? Telecommunication Services to provide healthcare are available to you because your health care insurance payer wants to keep you healthy and detect any unhealthy behavior which can be treated in a timely manner. Most Health insurance payers are now offering you and your healthcare provider the ability to Collect, store and interpret securely your physiologic data (e.g. blood pressure, glucose monitoring, body weight) and non physiological data using new technology.


How to enter the elements of services?Telecommunication Services to provide healthcare Services include 24-hours-a-day, 7-days-a-week access to a healthcare application on your smartphone, through an app, you are able to enter your non- physiological data or through application programming interface (API) devices which transmit tour physiological data directly to your physician’s data repository, which will be monitored by your provider or his/her designated train healthcare worker. Your provider will make management decisions based on your physiological and non physiological data and would ask you to act accordingly.

Beneficiary Acknowledgment and Authorization

By signing this Agreement, you agree to the following:You consent to the Provider providing Telecommunication Services to provide healthcare:

  • You may receive an API device or SaMD( software application Medical Device) at no cost to you, you agree to use these devices at least 16 day per month. Most Health insurance payers are now paying for Telecommunication services at no cost or minimal cost to you. The cost-sharing will apply according to the law.
  • You consent to the Provider providing CCM Services to you.
  • You authorize electronic communication of your medical information with other treating providers as part of coordination of your care.
  • You acknowledge that only one practitioner can furnish CCM Services to you during a calendar month,
  • You understand that cost-sharing will apply to CCM Services, so that you may be billed for a portion of CCM Services even though CCM Services will not involve a face-to-face meeting with the Provider. If your supplemental insurance does not cover the remaining cost, the remaining will be billed to you for the service.

Beneficiary Rights

You have the following rights with respect to Telecommunication Services to provide healthcare

  • You have the right to stop Telecommunication Services to provide healthcare at any time by revoking this Agreement effective at the end of the then-current month. You may revoke this agreement verbally or in writing.
  • Telecommunication services are non face to face services, most insurance pay for these services, and cost sharing is applied.
  • I understand that there are alternatives to Telecommunication Services to provide healthcare and I may elect, at any time, for a direct consultation in person by any healthcare provider at any time
  • The provider will provide you with a written or electronic copy of your care plan.
  • You have the right to stop CCM Services at any time by revoking this Agreement effective at the end of the then current month. You may revoke this agreement verbally or in writing. Upon receipt of your revocation, the Provider will give you written confirmation (including the effective date) of the revocation.

messages.text:
“Dear Patients,

This is your doctor, [Dr. Name], with [Practice Name]

I’m happy to inform you that we have partnered with Health Wealth Safe, a Digital Health Platform, to help monitor your health and wellness in between your regular office visits. Remote Patient Monitoring and Chronic Care Management are covered by most health insurance plans.

A Care Manager from Health Wealth Safe will be contacting you to explain the services and assist with the enrollment process.

As a participant in this program, you will qualify for up to three medical devices. A blood pressure monitor, a bariatric weight scale, or a glucometer which includes a lifetime supply of strips and lancets.

I believe adding these services will help me keep you healthier and identify problems before they become serious.

Once again, I am [Dr. Name] asking you to enroll in these new services. I will explain more about these services at your next appointment, however,for now, contact Health Wealth Safe at 1-877-581-8810 for any additional questions.”

When you are ready to record, press the microphone button. Before you submit the recording, listen to it to make sure the quality is good.

labels.hwsVoiceRecording:
“Dear Patients,

This is your doctor, [Dr. Name], with [Practice Name]

I’m happy to inform you that we have partnered with Health Wealth Safe, a Digital Health Platform, to help monitor your health and wellness in between your regular office visits. Remote Patient Monitoring and Chronic Care Management are covered by most health insurance plans.

A Care Manager from Health Wealth Safe will be contacting you to explain the services and assist with the enrollment process.

As a participant in this program, you will qualify for up to three medical devices. A blood pressure monitor, a bariatric weight scale, or a glucometer which includes a lifetime supply of strips and lancets.

I believe adding these services will help me keep you healthier and identify problems before they become serious.

Once again, I am [Dr. Name] asking you to enroll in these new services. I will explain more about these services at your next appointment, however,for now, contact Health Wealth Safe at 1-877-581-8810 for any additional questions.”

When you are ready to record, press the microphone button. Before you submit the recording, listen to it to make sure the quality is good.
